      "writtenOn": "2020-08-19T04:31:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Updated the description.\nIt should be the input gitiles commit but not strictly input.gitiles_commit\nHowever, the actual commit used when searching the build is read from the gitiles buildset tag.\nFrom what I can find, buildbucket set the tag to input.gitiles_commit.\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:appengine/cr-buildbucket/creation.py;l\u003d265\n\nscheduler also set the tag to the triggering commit when the build is trigger by gitiles.\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/scheduler/appengine/engine/policy/request_builder.go;l\u003d104\n\nI can also update the comment to say that it depends on the buildset tag. WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "9c4eab18_effec068",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 42,
        "endChar": 37
      },
